fields.name: measRate
fields.description: The elapsed time between GNSS measurements (ms). Defines the measurement rate (e.g. 100 ms = 10 Hz).

fields.name: navRate
fields.description: The ratio between the number of measurements and the number of navigation solutions. Maximum value 127.

fields.name: timeRef
fields.description: The time system to which measurements are aligned. 0: UTC, 1: GPS, 2: GLONASS, 3: BeiDou, 4: Galileo, 5: NavIC.

valid_variations.reason: Older firmware/protocol versions documented in these manuals did not yet support NavIC (value 5) for time alignment.

adjudication.reasoning: All 8 extractions agree on the binary structure (3 fields of U2 type, total length 6 bytes). The only differences are in the description text for 'timeRef', where older documents (HPG 1.13, ZED-F9H) list values 0-4, and newer documents include 0-5 (adding NavIC). Extraction 8 (M8) includes NavIC in the description, which is unusual for M8 but structurally consistent. The canonical structure uses the superset of features (including NavIC).
